    "title": "The Charlotte Knights are celebrating 'Read Across America Day' | wcnc.com",
    "text": "CHARLOTTE, N.C. — The Knights and Homer the Dragon are celebrating “Read Across America Day” and will be reading to local Charlotte area kids at three schools this Friday morning. The schools on Friday are: Unity Classical Charter, Lake Wylie Elementary & Sterling Elementary.\nThe Charlotte Knights are also gearing up for opening Day of the 2024 season which is set for Tuesday, April 2. This year marks the 10th season in Truist Field history and the Knights have welcomed over 5 million fans through the gates since opening in 2014.\nTruist Field is nominated as one of the best ballparks in Minor League Baseball and there is currently a vote going on at USA TODAY. Click here to vote!\nTheir 2024 promo calendar has been released, and features 24 fireworks shows, five celebrity guests, bobblehead giveaways and more this year! Find more information here .\nCharlotte Today is a local lifestyle and entertainment show where you'll learn everything about the Queen City with hosts Mia Atkins and Eugene Robinson on WCNC Charlotte live weekdays at 11 a.m.\nFrom what’s trending to local restaurants, events and entertainment, you’ll find it all on this show.\nCharlotte Today also features sponsored content by local and national businesses. Are you a business interested in advertising with us ? Go to WCNC.com/advertise or call now (214) 977-6001\nIf you have a question for the Charlotte Today team, feel free to email them at charlottetoday@wcnc.com\nMake sure to follow Charlotte Today on Facebook , Twitter and Instagram .\nGet to know hosts Mia and Eugene by reading their bio pages and following them on social media.",
